--> CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS 

IF • ELIF • ELSE in Python
These are called:
      --> Conditional Statements

      --> Used when computer needs to make decisions.

      --> Example:
             if marks > 35 → Pass
             else → Fail

1. IF STATEMENT :

--> Runs code only if condition is True.

--> Syntax
if condition:
    code

--> Example
age = 18
if age >= 18:
    print("Eligible to vote")

--> Output:
Eligible to vote

--> Because:
18 >= 18
is True.


2. ELSE STATEMENT :

--> Runs when condition is False.

--> Example
age = 16
if age >= 18:
    print("Eligible")
else:
    print("Not Eligible")

--> Output:
Not Eligible


3. ELIF STATEMENT :

--> elif means:
         --> else if

--> Used for multiple conditions.

--> Example
marks = 75
if marks >= 90:
    print("Grade A")

elif marks >= 75:
    print("Grade B")

else:
    print("Grade C")

--> Output:
      Grade B


                         FLOW UNDERSTANDING :

                            if condition True
                                  ↓
                             run if block

                              otherwise
                                 ↓
                              check elif
 
                              otherwise
                                 ↓
                              run else
